choices.text:
the fact that I am always trying to stop my clock, I want to lengthen my life and live it forever, for I am saddened by the idea that once I pass, my life will cease. Another major issue is balancing where I am obligated and have zero choice in decisions. I believe that as an adult, I need to let myself flourish and grow, and not over think things when its too late to decide. Whilst I allow myself to rule over my tiny empire, my eye is always on controlling things. As a adult, I’ve realized that I should be looking more towards controlling my over-protectiveness for others. I honestly believe that sometimes, with age, should always be accompanied by freedom as a concept to further ones self as a individual and a whole.

Victoria Munoko (14)

When I transitioned, suddenly, to being an adult I realised a lot about the person I acted to be. I acted carefully to be the most appropriate, and well-liked woman I could be. Because that’s all I have ever known.

I have become great at being a statistically beautiful woman, and that’s honestly disappointing as an opening to adulthood.

But I have also learned that beauty shouldn’t matter as much as I’m made to believe it does. I have learned far bigger lessons and that is wonderful.
